FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776927916
OL,3,CWhy hay fever misery last two weeks
OL,4,Clonger than in the 90s
OL,6,FSymptoms are usually worse when the
OL,7,Fweather is warm, humid and windy, when
OL,8,Fthe pollen count is at its highest
OL,9,Fover summer.
OL,11,FThe new report, published in The
OL,12,FLancet Public Health, says climate
OL,13,Fchange is shifting the flowering
OL,14,Fseason of plants that release
OL,15,Fallergenic pollen.
OL,17,FThey examined changes in the timing
OL,18,Fand intensity of birch, alder and
OL,19,Folive pollen season.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776927916
OL,3,CWhy hay fever misery last two weeks
OL,4,Clonger than in the 90s
OL,6,FThey found an earlier season start of
OL,7,Fone to two weeks was detected for all
OL,8,Fallergenic trees between 2015 and
OL,9,F2024, compared with 1991 to 2000.
OL,11,FDr Samantha Walker, director of
OL,12,Fresearch and innovation at Asthma and
OL,13,FLung UK, warned: "A longer pollen
OL,14,Fseason will bring more misery for
OL,15,Fpeople with hay fever."
OL,17,FAnne Biggs, deputy head of clinical
OL,18,Fservices at Allergy UK, said: "While
OL,19,Ffor some their symptoms can be mild,
OL,20,Ffor many their hay fever symptoms
OL,21,Fimpacts their quality of life.
OL,26,@zD@_OU
